Exploring DHCP

Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol - works at the application layer of the OSI Model


Dynamically assigns IP addresses on a local area network

Uses UDP for transport

Client uses port 68
Server uses port 67

DORA Process

  Client -> Server = Discovery         TIME
  Server -> Client = Offer              |
  Client -> Server = Request            |  
  Server -> Client = Acknowledge        V

